				<td colspan="2"><span>I had leveled past where I needed to worry about it before any changes happened with my bard, but I do know that many skills can not be trained to your level cap at a trainer anymore... to force you to learn through use.  This is even true of melee skills in many cases.  With my berserker I am leveling currently I can hit a new level, and go to a GM and some skills I simply can not train anymore, I get the message about training to the limit etc etc, yet when I got battle creatures I DO get skill increases through use.  This *could* be the situation here, but I do not know, since I am not leveling a new bard (and do not plan to with 66 levels and 140 AAs behind me, lol).  
<br />

<br />
So keep an eye on it, it may be a new deviation to level caps, or it may just be a bug due to the new restrictive code on spending training points at guilds, or it could be exceptional bad luck with a few people not getting skill gains for a long period of time... I know for example defense caps at 252, however mine was stuck at 250 for over 2 months, then at 251 for another month... and this was back when I liked to split tank single adds instead of mezzing, so I got hit a LOT. (normal LDoNs at levels 60-65 I could do this easily... I wish I could in hards and GoD etc etc, but alas, not yet, but I digress...</span></td>
